machine learning techniques \& complex methods relying on design sciences, experimental games and simulations


computational modeling to simulate the systems of interest: “computational modeling reinforces the system view that models are for continually estimating a range of probable trajectories that represent a best guess at any given moment.” (Leach and Bou Zeineddine, 2021, p. 360)




statistics


“a key statistical approach in systems research is the comparison of model fit, power, and robustness (to perturbations in the system)” (Leach and Bou Zeineddine, 2021, p. 360)




“A shared view of emotion in context as a system of systems should enable the diverse strands of work in this area to “speak a common language,” integrating the knowledge we have acquired thus far (see McGuire, 1983).” (Leach and Bou Zeineddine, 2021, p. 360)

},
